WEST JORDAN — Police are investigating a double homicide that occurred overnight.
On Saturday afternoon they confirmed that husband and wife Tony and Katherine Butterfield, 31 and 30, were found dead at a home near 3200 West and 6900 South.
Police responded to a call about possible gunshots about 1:15 a.m., said West Jordan Police Sgt.
